This paper is primarily focused on analyzing the performance of Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs) for face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the generalization ability of DCNNs, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses synthetic data to study the effect of dataset biases, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
